author: CNN
description: Neighbors filled the streets and surrounded Border Patrol agents during the arrest of a nearby construction worker in a Chicago neighborhood. Two US citizens were arrested for assaulting and impeding a federal officer, the agency said.
title: Border Patrol agents arrest undocumented immigrant and two US citizens

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper points out the similarities between Maine Senate candidate Graham Platner's cover-up of his Nazi-linked chest tattoo and a meme from a British comedy show depicting a Nazi soldier realizing the badge on his cap is a symbol of evil.
title: What a 2000s meme has to do with a US Senate race

author: CNN
description:
A rare and catastrophic Category 5 storm is bearing down on the island nation. Hurricane Melissa rapidly intensified over the weekend and is now the strongest storm ever forecast to strike Jamaica is expected to unleash devastating winds, storm surge and extreme rain, setting off life-threatening flooding and landslides.
#cnn #news
title: Melissa forecast to be strongest to ever hit Jamaica

author: CNN
description: Video taken October 26 by a hurricane hunter shows what the inside of Hurricane Melissa’s eye looks like #cnn #news #shorts
title: Inside the eye of Hurricane Melissa

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump met with Japanese Emperor Naruhito in a closed-door meeting, entirely out of the public view. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery explains why the Japan’s imperial family is always private. #cnn #news
title: Why is Japan’s imperial family famously private?

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump is expected to meet with Chinese leader Xi Jinping this Thursday in South Korea, wrapping up the US president’s diplomatic tour of Southeast Asia with one of America’s most important trade partners.

On Sunday, Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent expressed optimism ahead of Xi and Trump’s meeting. “I think we’ve reached a substantial framework for the two leaders who will meet next Thursday … that tariffs will be averted,” Bessent said on ABC’s “This Week” from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
Dana Bash discusses with her "Inside Politics" panel: CNN's Manu Raju, the AP's Seung Min Kim, CNN's Isaac Dovere, and Puck's Julia Ioffe. #CNN #News
title: Trump promises new tariffs on Canada, while the US and China have reached a trade deal framework

author: CNN
description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom and former Vice President Kamala Harris answer questions about their potential runs for the presidency in 2028. #CNN #News
title: Gavin Newsom and Kamala Harris talk about 2028 runs

author: CNN
description: The Sudanese paramilitary Rapid Support Forces claim they’ve captured the army’s headquarters in the city of El Fasher, which would be a major victory for the rebel force in the country’s civil war. #cnn #news
title: RSF rebels claim to capture key city in Sudan

author: CNN
description: Argentina's President Javier Milei has led his La Libertad Avanza party to a landslide victory in the midterm elections. Milei has vowed to keep pushing through his radical overhaul of the economy, despite widespread discontent with his deep austerity measures. #CNN #News
title: Milei wins big in Argentina’s midterm elections

author: CNN
description: Rafiq Deeb is looking for bodies of his wife and four children under the rubble after Israel bombed their home in Gaza nearly 2 years ago. They are among more than 10,000 people whose bodies are still trapped beneath mounds of concrete and twisted metal, according to Gaza’s Civil Defense. CNN’s Jeremy Diamond reports.
title: Thousands of deceased Palestinians trapped under Gaza’s rubble

author: CNN
description:
Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program, or SNAP, benefits, relied upon by 42 million Americans are expected to run out November 1, due to the government shutdown.

CNN's Zain Asher speaks with Kyle Waide, President and CEO of Atlanta Community Food Bank, on the shutdown's impact. #CNN #News
title: 42 million Americans at risk as food assistance running out

author: CNN
description: Air traffic controller staffing shortages worsened over the weekend as the nation’s government shutdown hit its fourth week, leading to delays and anxiety, and experts say it won’t get better until air traffic controllers get paid.  #CNN #News
title: Airport delays spike amid air traffic controller shortages

author: CNN
description: Sami Hamdi, a British commentator, was taken into custody by ICE at San Francisco airport on Sunday. Hamdi, who has been openly critical of Israel, was in the middle of a speaking tour in the US but has now had his visa revoked. In a post on X, a Homeland Security official said, “Under President Trump, those who support terrorism and undermine American national security will not be allowed to work or visit this country.” #cnn #samihamdi #ICE
title: British commentator Sami Hamdi detained by ICE

author: CNN
description:
Jamaica is preparing for record amounts of rain and intense winds as Hurricane Melissa intensified over the weekend. Melissa is expected to be the strongest hurricane to ever strike the island.

#CNN #News #HurricaneMelissa #Jamaica
title: Hurricane Melissa closes in on Jamaica

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down the numbers on how Americans feel about Canada, and how Canadians feel about the United States. Also, CNN's Sara Sidner speaks with Rep. Brendan Boyle (D-PA), ranking member on the House Budget Committee. #CNN #News
title: Trump, tariffs and Canada: CNN's Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said that he received an MRI scan during a recent trip to Walter Reed National Military Medical Center – marking the first time he has provided a reason for his second medical exam this year and raising new questions about the president’s health. CNN’s Kristen Holmes reports and CNN medical analyst Dr. Jonathan Reiner reacts to the news.   #CNN #News
title: Trump says he received an MRI during trip to Walter Reed medical center

author: CNN
description: CNN Senior Political Commentator Adam Kinzinger and CNN Political Commentators Brad Todd, Xochitl Hinojosa, and Kristen Soltis Anderson join Jake to discuss whether Trump could pay a political price for tearing down the East Wing of the White House.  #CNN #News
title: Kinzinger: East Wing demolition ‘emblematic of how Donald Trump has run his presidency’

author: CNN
description: CNN's Betsy Klein reports from Tokyo where President Trump has arrived to a warm welcome on the second stop on his Asia diplomacy tour. #CNN #news
title: Trump receives warm welcome in Japan

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump is in Japan, the second stop on his Asia diplomacy tour, where he visited Emperor Naruhito at Tokyo’s Imperial Palace. On Tuesday, he will meet Japan’s first female prime minister, Sanae Takaichi.  In Malaysia, US-China trade negotiators reported major progress on a potential trade deal, easing tensions before Trump’s expected meeting with Chinese leader Xi Jinping later this week.

CNN senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes and CNN international correspondent Hanako Montgomery report from Tokyo, and CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Jeff Moon, former assistant US Trade Representative to China in the Obama administration. #CNN #News
title: Trump in Japan as US reaches tentative trade deal with China

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump raised new questions about his health after he told reporters on Air Force One that he received an MRI scan during a recent trip to Walter Reed National Military Medical Center. The president declined to say why he received the MRI.

#cnn #news #trump #airforce1 #health
title: Trump reveals he got an MRI during recent exam

author: CNN
description: Melissa rapidly intensified over the weekend and is now a rare Category 5 hurricane with 160 mph winds. The National Hurricane Center expects it to make landfall in Jamaica on Tuesday morning as the strongest hurricane on record to strike the island.  #CNN #News
title: Hurricane Melissa is now a rare Category 5 storm as it closes in on Jamaica

author: CNN
description: Japan's new prime minister, Sanae Takaichi, makes her debut on the global stage as US President Donald Trump arrives in Tokyo. With billions in trade and defense commitments on the table, talks come at a pivotal moment for both leaders. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery breaks down the key themes Trump and Takaichi are expected to discuss at their high-stakes meeting. #CNN #News #Japan
title: First big test for Japan’s new leader: Meeting Trump

author: CNN
description: Día de los Muertos (Day of the Dead) celebrations have begun in Mexico City, with hundreds taking to the streets dressed as La Catrina, the iconic Mexican skeleton figure. Day of the Dead is celebrated on November 2, following days of festivities. #cnn #dayofthedead #mexicocity
title: Hundreds celebrate Day of the Dead in Mexico City

author: CNN
description: A police officer performed CPR on an unconscious infant rescued from an overturned vehicle after a crash in Fort Worth, Texas. The infant and a woman driver are in stable condition and are expected to make a full recovery, according to police. #CNN #News
title: Dramatic moment of police rescuing infant trapped underneath car

author: CNN
description: Video shows the moment a driver in Oklahoma City nearly collided with a plane that was crash-landing on a road. National Guard officials are investigating the cause of the incident.
title: Car dashcam captures near-collision with US Air Force plane
